## Authentication

### Two-Legged OAuth (Client Credentials)

For server-to-server integrations using client credentials:

```typescript
import { Client } from '{{langConfig.packageName}}';

const client = new Client({
  domain: 'your-institution.blackboard.com',
  clientId: 'your-client-id',
  clientSecret: 'your-client-secret',
});
```

### Three-Legged OAuth (Authorization Code + PKCE)

For user-delegated access (e.g., acting on behalf of a student or instructor):

```typescript
import { OAuth2Client } from '{{langConfig.packageName}}';

const auth = new OAuth2Client({
  baseUrl: 'https://your-institution.blackboard.com',
  clientId: 'your-client-id',
  clientSecret: 'your-client-secret',
  tokenEndpoint: '{{auth.twoLegged.tokenEndpoint}}',
});

// Step 1: Generate the authorization URL with PKCE
const { url, codeVerifier } = await auth.getAuthorizationUrl({
  redirectUri: 'https://your-app.com/callback',
  scope: 'read',
  state: 'random-csrf-token',
});
// Redirect the user to `url`

// Step 2: After the user authorizes, exchange the code
await auth.exchangeCode(code, 'https://your-app.com/callback', codeVerifier);

// Step 3: Use the authenticated client
const client = new Client({
  domain: 'your-institution.blackboard.com',
  clientId: 'your-client-id',
  clientSecret: 'your-client-secret',
});
client.setAccessToken(auth.getToken());
```

## Quick Start

```typescript
// List courses
const courses = await client.courses.list();
console.log(courses);

// Get a single course
const course = await client.courses.get('externalId:INTRO-101');
console.log(course.name);
```

## Error Handling

```typescript
import { NotFoundError, RateLimitError, APIError } from '{{langConfig.packageName}}';

try {
  const course = await client.courses.get('_invalid_id_');
} catch (err) {
  if (err instanceof NotFoundError) {
    console.log('Course not found');
  } else if (err instanceof RateLimitError) {
    console.log(`Rate limited — retry after ${err.retryAfter}s`);
  } else if (err instanceof APIError) {
    console.log(`API error ${err.status}: ${err.message}`);
  }
}
```

## Pagination

Paginated methods return async iterables:

```typescript
for await (const course of client.courses.list()) {
  console.log(course.name);
}
```

